text: Azmi Mohamed Megahed (; 15 April 1950 - 12 September 2020) was an Egyptian volleyball player. He competed in the men's tournament at the 1976 Summer Olympics. He was born in Dakahlia, Egypt. Megahed died on 12 September 2020 in a hospital in Cairo due to COVID-19 at the age of 70. ==References== Category:1950 births Category:2020 deaths Category:Deaths from the COVID-19 pandemic in Cairo Category:Volleyball players Category:Olympians for Egypt
